Class Car

java.lang.Object
Car
public class Car
extends java.lang.Object
This class represents a car object and stores properties of a car.
Author:
Karim R. Sammouri

    • Car

      public Car​(java.lang.String owner, java.lang.String make, java.lang.String model, int yearModel, float fuelLevel, int speed, boolean start)
      Workhorse constructor.
      Parameters:
      owner - Owner of the car.
      make - Make of the car.
      model - Model of the car.
      yearModel - Year model of the car. The year cannot be greater than 2021 and smaller than 1885.
      fuelLevel - Fuel level of the car. The fuel level ranges between 0 and 1.0.
      speed - Current speed of the car. The speed cannot be a negative number and the maximum speed of a car is 250 mph.
      start - The current state of the engine. True if the engine is turned on and false otherwise.

    • accelerate

      public boolean accelerate()
      This method increases the car's speed by 3 miles per hour if the car's engine is on, the fuel level is at least 0.5, and the speed is less than 250. If the car is already at max speed, acceleration will not increase speed but decrese the fuel level.
      Returns:
      True if the car was able to be accelerated, false otherwise.

    • brake

      public boolean brake()
      This method decreases the car speed by 3 if the speed is at least 3. If the car's speed is less than 3, the speed is set to zero.
      Returns:
      True if the car was able to be slowed, false otherwise.

    • isGasTankEmpty

      public boolean isGasTankEmpty()
      This method returns true if the fuel level of the car is less than 0.5, false otherwise.
      Returns:
      True if fuel level of the car is below 0, false otherwise.

    • sameOwner
